modules.description: Handles database statement creation and execution, including parameterized queries and result retrieval. Operates on database connections, SQL statements, and result sets, supporting both named and positional parameters. Processes query outcomes, retrieves affected rows and auto-increment IDs, and manages result metadata and cleanup.

Provides functions to execute SQL queries, fetch results as rows, and manage database connections using MySQL protocol. Works with connection parameters, query strings, and result sets represented as lists of tuples. Used to retrieve user data from a database, insert new records, and update existing entries in a relational database system.

Manages database interactions through statement execution, parameterized queries, and result handling. Supports named and positional parameters, tracks affected rows and auto-increment values, and extracts metadata from query results. Executes SQL commands and processes returned data efficiently. Example tasks include inserting records with generated IDs and fetching structured result sets.
